<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.38-39_0001a" />

<opener>
<dateline><del>May 13</del>
June 1, 1970</dateline>

<salute>Dear Slade:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I was in Columbia writing when your letter was forwarded to me.</p>

<p>As for the proposed collection of Essays, there is no possibility of early publication. I even think of their appearance after I'm living in that beautiful <del><unclear>Mansion</unclear></del>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.38-39_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
<fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>

mansion I have in Heaven!! Of course, they may appear<del/> while I'm living, but I don't care; I just want the Essays preserved.</p>

<p>I have decided to complete my "Autobiography" before publishing any of it. This seems the wiser way. I'll be busy on the <hi rend="underline">Adult Section</hi> most of the coming year.</p>

<p>Dr. Aly's Biography of <hi rend="caps">J &#8212; G</hi> &#8212; Neihardt is complete and the <hi rend="caps">MS</hi><del/> is in the 

<fw type="curatorial">38</fw>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.38-39_0002a"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

hands of the publisher. It is a large <unclear>work</unclear> &#8212; 1000 pages of <hi rend="caps">MS</hi> &#8212; and God alone knows what the publisher may decide, altho<sic>although</sic> the author has a contract. It <hi rend="double underline">is</hi> a remarkably <hi rend="underline">fine piece of work.</hi> Hilda pronounces it "magnificent." It is the result of <hi rend="double underline">ten</hi> years of scholarly research. And devotion.</p>

<p>It <hi rend="double underline">should</hi> apper<sic>appear</sic> in 1971.<del/></p>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.38-39_0002b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-4-</fw>
<fw type="curatorial">2<unclear/></fw>

<p>Well, the poor cock-eyed world is in a heluva dither, isn't <del><unclear>it?</unclear></del> it? <hi rend="underline">How</hi> can we get out of this idiotic war &#8212; 10000 miles from home and <hi rend="double underline">no</hi> possibility of winning a <del><unclear>victory</unclear></del> victory!??!</p>
<closer>
<salute>Kindest thoughts &#8212;</salute>

<salute>Your affectionate old friend &#8212;</salute>

<signed>John Neihardt</signed>
</closer>

<postscript><p>The "Red Wind" <hi rend="double underline">is</hi> blowing, across the world!! See my poem written years before the Russian Revolution</p></postscript>

<fw type="curatorial">39</fw>

</div1>
